{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":446,"text":"I am a neuroscientist"},{"time":2071,"text":"with a mixed background in physics and medicine."},{"time":5882,"text":"My lab at the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology"},{"time":10923,"text":"focuses on spinal cord injury,"},{"time":14113,"text":"which affects more than 50,000 people"},{"time":16844,"text":"around the world every year,"},{"time":19534,"text":"with dramatic consequences for affected individuals,"},{"time":23140,"text":"whose life literally shatters"},{"time":25373,"text":"in a matter of a handful of seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28608,"text":"And for me, the Man of Steel,"},{"time":31666,"text":"Christopher Reeve,"},{"time":33870,"text":"has best raised the awareness"},{"time":35960,"text":"on the distress of spinal cord injured people."},{"time":38875,"text":"And this is how I started my own personal journey"},{"time":42014,"text":"in this field of research,"},{"time":43513,"text":"working with the Christopher and Dana Reeve Foundation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46950,"text":"I still remember this decisive moment."},{"time":51546,"text":"It was just at the end of a regular day of work"},{"time":53497,"text":"with the foundation."},{"time":55040,"text":"Chris addressed us, the scientists and experts,"},{"time":59692,"text":"\"You have to be more pragmatic."},{"time":63285,"text":"When leaving your laboratory tomorrow,"},{"time":65637,"text":"I want you to stop by the rehabilitation center"},{"time":68541,"text":"to watch injured people"},{"time":70150,"text":"fighting to take a step,"},{"time":72175,"text":"struggling to maintain their trunk."},{"time":74816,"text":"And when you go home,"},{"time":76229,"text":"think of what you are going to change in your research"},{"time":78639,"text":"on the following day to make their lives better.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":82207,"text":"These words, they stuck with me."},{"time":86260,"text":"This was more than 10 years ago,"},{"time":88651,"text":"but ever since, my laboratory has followed"},{"time":91418,"text":"the pragmatic approach to recovery"},{"time":93381,"text":"after spinal cord injury."},{"time":95792,"text":"And my first step in this direction"},{"time":97833,"text":"was to develop a new model of spinal cord injury"},{"time":101122,"text":"that would more closely mimic some of the key features of human injury"},{"time":104769,"text":"while offering well-controlled experimental conditions."},{"time":108141,"text":"And for this purpose, we placed two hemisections"},{"time":110708,"text":"on opposite sides of the body."},{"time":112123,"text":"They completely interrupt the communication"},{"time":114268,"text":"between the brain and the spinal cord,"},{"time":116850,"text":"thus leading to complete and permanent paralysis"},{"time":119560,"text":"of the leg."},{"time":121327,"text":"But, as observed, after most injuries in humans,"},{"time":125218,"text":"there is this intervening gap of intact neural tissue"},{"time":128168,"text":"through which recovery can occur."},{"time":130871,"text":"But how to make it happen?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133912,"text":"Well, the classical approach"},{"time":137273,"text":"consists of applying intervention"},{"time":139909,"text":"that would promote the growth of the severed fiber"},{"time":142819,"text":"to the original target."},{"time":144927,"text":"And while this certainly remained the key for a cure,"},{"time":148678,"text":"this seemed extraordinarily complicated to me."},{"time":152193,"text":"To reach clinical fruition rapidly,"},{"time":154918,"text":"it was obvious:"},{"time":156478,"text":"I had to think about the problem differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160398,"text":"It turned out that more than 100 years of research"},{"time":163506,"text":"on spinal cord physiology,"},{"time":165147,"text":"starting with the Nobel Prize Sherrington,"},{"time":167472,"text":"had shown that"},{"time":169279,"text":"the spinal cord, below most injuries,"},{"time":171514,"text":"contained all the necessary and sufficient neural networks"},{"time":174767,"text":"to coordinate locomotion,"},{"time":177087,"text":"but because input from the brain is interrupted,"},{"time":180046,"text":"they are in a nonfunctional state, like kind of dormant."},{"time":183214,"text":"My idea: We awaken this network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187546,"text":"And at the time, I was a post-doctoral fellow in Los Angeles,"},{"time":191833,"text":"after completing my Ph.D. in France,"},{"time":194399,"text":"where independent thinking"},{"time":196308,"text":"is not necessarily promoted."},{"time":199415,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":201242,"text":"I was afraid to talk to my new boss,"},{"time":204995,"text":"but decided to muster up my courage."},{"time":207388,"text":"I knocked at the door of my wonderful advisor,"},{"time":210045,"text":"Reggie Edgerton, to share my new idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214036,"text":"He listened to me carefully,"},{"time":216286,"text":"and responded with a grin."},{"time":219227,"text":"\"Why don't you try?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":221270,"text":"And I promise to you,"},{"time":223395,"text":"this was such an important moment in my career,"},{"time":226750,"text":"when I realized that the great leader"},{"time":229185,"text":"believed in young people and new ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232178,"text":"And this was the idea:"},{"time":233786,"text":"I'm going to use a simplistic metaphor"},{"time":236452,"text":"to explain to you this complicated concept."},{"time":238578,"text":"Imagine that the locomotor system is a car."},{"time":243344,"text":"The engine is the spinal cord."},{"time":245590,"text":"The transmission is interrupted. The engine is turned off."},{"time":248848,"text":"How could we re-engage the engine?"},{"time":251855,"text":"First, we have to provide the fuel;"},{"time":254997,"text":"second, press the accelerator pedal;"},{"time":257340,"text":"third, steer the car."},{"time":259278,"text":"It turned out that there are known neural pathways"},{"time":261040,"text":"coming from the brain that play this very function"},{"time":263994,"text":"during locomotion."},{"time":265376,"text":"My idea: Replace this missing input"},{"time":268091,"text":"to provide the spinal cord"},{"time":269493,"text":"with the kind of intervention"},{"time":270889,"text":"that the brain would deliver naturally in order to walk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275619,"text":"For this, I leveraged 20 years of past research in neuroscience,"},{"time":280058,"text":"first to replace the missing fuel"},{"time":282822,"text":"with pharmacological agents"},{"time":284890,"text":"that prepare the neurons in the spinal cord to fire,"},{"time":288370,"text":"and second, to mimic the accelerator pedal"},{"time":292425,"text":"with electrical stimulation."},{"time":293905,"text":"So here imagine an electrode"},{"time":296074,"text":"implanted on the back of the spinal cord"},{"time":298480,"text":"to deliver painless stimulation."},{"time":300742,"text":"It took many years, but eventually we developed"},{"time":303574,"text":"an electrochemical neuroprosthesis"},{"time":306131,"text":"that transformed the neural network"},{"time":307897,"text":"in the spinal cord from dormant to a highly functional state."},{"time":312903,"text":"Immediately, the paralyzed rat can stand."},{"time":319183,"text":"As soon as the treadmill belt starts moving,"},{"time":321510,"text":"the animal shows coordinated movement of the leg,"},{"time":325316,"text":"but without the brain."},{"time":327294,"text":"Here what I call \"the spinal brain\""},{"time":329284,"text":"cognitively processes sensory information"},{"time":332406,"text":"arising from the moving leg"},{"time":334301,"text":"and makes decisions as to how to activate the muscle"},{"time":337996,"text":"in order to stand, to walk, to run,"},{"time":341386,"text":"and even here, while sprinting,"},{"time":343498,"text":"instantly stand"},{"time":345795,"text":"if the treadmill stops moving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348258,"text":"This was amazing."},{"time":349595,"text":"I was completely fascinated by this locomotion"},{"time":352982,"text":"without the brain,"},{"time":355477,"text":"but at the same time so frustrated."},{"time":359132,"text":"This locomotion was completely involuntary."},{"time":361525,"text":"The animal had virtually no control over the legs."},{"time":364890,"text":"Clearly, the steering system was missing."},{"time":369010,"text":"And it then became obvious from me"},{"time":370902,"text":"that we had to move away"},{"time":372250,"text":"from the classical rehabilitation paradigm,"},{"time":375622,"text":"stepping on a treadmill,"},{"time":377344,"text":"and develop conditions that would encourage"},{"time":380564,"text":"the brain to begin voluntary control over the leg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385797,"text":"With this in mind, we developed a completely new"},{"time":389182,"text":"robotic system to support the rat"},{"time":392412,"text":"in any direction of space."},{"time":394938,"text":"Imagine, this is really cool."},{"time":397113,"text":"So imagine the little 200-gram rat"},{"time":400944,"text":"attached at the extremity of this 200-kilo robot,"},{"time":404645,"text":"but the rat does not feel the robot."},{"time":407217,"text":"The robot is transparent,"},{"time":409289,"text":"just like you would hold a young child"},{"time":411651,"text":"during the first insecure steps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414015,"text":"Let me summarize: The rat received"},{"time":417569,"text":"a paralyzing lesion of the spinal cord."},{"time":420014,"text":"The electrochemical neuroprosthesis enabled"},{"time":422604,"text":"a highly functional state of the spinal locomotor networks."},{"time":426811,"text":"The robot provided the safe environment"},{"time":430577,"text":"to allow the rat to attempt anything"},{"time":432540,"text":"to engage the paralyzed legs."},{"time":435222,"text":"And for motivation, we used what I think"},{"time":438047,"text":"is the most powerful pharmacology of Switzerland:"},{"time":441881,"text":"fine Swiss chocolate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444188,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":447110,"text":"Actually, the first results were very, very,"},{"time":451673,"text":"very disappointing."},{"time":454308,"text":"Here is my best physical therapist"},{"time":464794,"text":"completely failing to encourage the rat"},{"time":467384,"text":"to take a single step,"},{"time":469445,"text":"whereas the same rat, five minutes earlier,"},{"time":472291,"text":"walked beautifully on the treadmill."},{"time":474597,"text":"We were so frustrated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476754,"text":"But you know, one of the most essential qualities"},{"time":479653,"text":"of a scientist is perseverance."},{"time":482129,"text":"We insisted. We refined our paradigm,"},{"time":485545,"text":"and after several months of training,"},{"time":487808,"text":"the otherwise paralyzed rat could stand,"},{"time":491614,"text":"and whenever she decided,"},{"time":493426,"text":"initiated full weight-bearing locomotion"},{"time":495758,"text":"to sprint towards the rewards."},{"time":499008,"text":"This is the first recovery ever observed"},{"time":502413,"text":"of voluntary leg movement"},{"time":504307,"text":"after an experimental lesion of the spinal cord"},{"time":506761,"text":"leading to complete and permanent paralysis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510222,"text":"In fact --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512209,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513929,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518308,"text":"In fact, not only could the rat initiate"},{"time":521402,"text":"and sustain locomotion on the ground,"},{"time":524079,"text":"they could even adjust leg movement,"},{"time":526360,"text":"for example, to resist gravity"},{"time":528716,"text":"in order to climb a staircase."},{"time":531340,"text":"I can promise you this was"},{"time":533290,"text":"such an emotional moment in my laboratory."},{"time":536399,"text":"It took us 10 years of hard work"},{"time":539142,"text":"to reach this goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541593,"text":"But the remaining question was, how?"},{"time":544144,"text":"I mean, how is it possible?"},{"time":545836,"text":"And here, what we found"},{"time":547514,"text":"was completely unexpected."},{"time":551190,"text":"This novel training paradigm"},{"time":555348,"text":"encouraged the brain to create new connections,"},{"time":559019,"text":"some relay circuits"},{"time":561921,"text":"that relay information from the brain"},{"time":564969,"text":"past the injury and restore cortical control"},{"time":568125,"text":"over the locomotor networks below the injury."},{"time":571566,"text":"And here, you can see one such example,"},{"time":574488,"text":"where we label the fibers coming from the brain in red."},{"time":577851,"text":"This blue neuron is connected with the locomotor center,"},{"time":581271,"text":"and what this constellation"},{"time":583634,"text":"of synaptic contacts means"},{"time":585985,"text":"is that the brain is reconnected with the locomotor center"},{"time":589784,"text":"with only one relay neuron."},{"time":593782,"text":"But the remodeling was not restricted"},{"time":595713,"text":"to the lesion area."},{"time":596800,"text":"It occurred throughout the central nervous system,"},{"time":600089,"text":"including in the brain stem,"},{"time":602407,"text":"where we observed up to 300-percent increase"},{"time":605669,"text":"in the density of fibers coming from the brain."},{"time":609428,"text":"We did not aim to repair the spinal cord,"},{"time":612955,"text":"yet we were able to promote"},{"time":615552,"text":"one of the more extensive remodeling"},{"time":617709,"text":"of axonal projections ever observed"},{"time":620178,"text":"in the central nervous system of adult mammal"},{"time":622439,"text":"after an injury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624984,"text":"And there is a very important message"},{"time":630053,"text":"hidden behind this discovery."},{"time":634496,"text":"They are the result of a young team"},{"time":637718,"text":"of very talented people:"},{"time":640110,"text":"physical therapists, neurobiologists, neurosurgeons,"},{"time":644568,"text":"engineers of all kinds,"},{"time":646767,"text":"who have achieved together"},{"time":648558,"text":"what would have been impossible by single individuals."},{"time":652201,"text":"This is truly a trans-disciplinary team."},{"time":655284,"text":"They are working so close to each other"},{"time":657472,"text":"that there is horizontal transfer of DNA."},{"time":660663,"text":"We are creating the next generation"},{"time":662286,"text":"of M.D.'s and engineers"},{"time":664527,"text":"capable of translating discoveries all the way"},{"time":666971,"text":"from bench to bedside."},{"time":669643,"text":"And me?"},{"time":671649,"text":"I am only the maestro who orchestrated this beautiful symphony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676196,"text":"Now, I am sure you are all wondering, aren't you,"},{"time":682999,"text":"will this help injured people?"},{"time":686763,"text":"Me too, every day."},{"time":690655,"text":"The truth is that we don't know enough yet."},{"time":694068,"text":"This is certainly not a cure for spinal cord injury,"},{"time":698292,"text":"but I begin to believe that this may lead"},{"time":701026,"text":"to an intervention to improve recovery"},{"time":703593,"text":"and people's quality of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706780,"text":"I would like you all"},{"time":709269,"text":"to take a moment and dream with me."},{"time":712896,"text":"Imagine a person just suffered a spinal cord injury."},{"time":718791,"text":"After a few weeks of recovery,"},{"time":721946,"text":"we will implant a programmable pump"},{"time":724306,"text":"to deliver a personalized pharmacological cocktail"},{"time":727339,"text":"directly to the spinal cord."},{"time":729781,"text":"At the same time, we will implant an electrode array,"},{"time":733044,"text":"a sort of second skin"},{"time":735151,"text":"covering the area of the spinal cord controlling leg movement,"},{"time":738711,"text":"and this array is attached to an electrical pulse generator"},{"time":741977,"text":"that delivers stimulations that are tailored"},{"time":744439,"text":"to the person's needs."},{"time":746625,"text":"This defines a personalized electrochemical neuroprosthesis"},{"time":751483,"text":"that will enable locomotion"},{"time":754234,"text":"during training with a newly designed supporting system."},{"time":758281,"text":"And my hope is that after several months of training,"},{"time":761564,"text":"there may be enough remodeling of residual connection"},{"time":763727,"text":"to allow locomotion without the robot,"},{"time":767396,"text":"maybe even without pharmacology or stimulation."},{"time":771174,"text":"My hope here is to be able to create"},{"time":773708,"text":"the personalized condition"},{"time":775973,"text":"to boost the plasticity of the brain"},{"time":778636,"text":"and the spinal cord."},{"time":780167,"text":"And this is a radically new concept"},{"time":782906,"text":"that may apply to other neurological disorders,"},{"time":786199,"text":"what I termed \"personalized neuroprosthetics,\""},{"time":790737,"text":"where by sensing and stimulating neural interfaces,"},{"time":793761,"text":"I implanted throughout the nervous system,"},{"time":797475,"text":"in the brain, in the spinal cord,"},{"time":800816,"text":"even in peripheral nerves,"},{"time":803572,"text":"based on patient-specific impairments."},{"time":806739,"text":"But not to replace the lost function, no --"},{"time":811347,"text":"to help the brain help itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814538,"text":"And I hope this enticed your imagination,"},{"time":817178,"text":"because I can promise to you"},{"time":819074,"text":"this is not a matter of whether this revolution will occur,"},{"time":822317,"text":"but when."},{"time":824109,"text":"And remember, we are only as great"},{"time":826357,"text":"as our imagination, as big as our dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829942,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831934,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}